  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 0e80ae96b3eb9177eea5c8f9dadbcda1, type: 3}
  m_Name: Spiner TN
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  displayText: "Spiner\r\nSigurd's danger Level: 30%\r\nClassification: Non-biological
    Entity (Unstable)\r\n\r\n\u201CI don\u2019t think this thing is alive.\r\nBut
    I\u2019m not convinced it\u2019s dead either.\u201D\r\n\u2014 REDACTED\r\n\r\nDescription\r\n\r\nThe
    Spiner is not a creature in the conventional sense.\r\nInitial examinations suggest
    an impossible aggregation of muscle fibers and bones, assembled without any recognizable
    or even logical structure. These components appear misaligned, fused, and stretched,
    as if pulled together under twisted tension.\r\n\r\nA thin membrane, similar
    to skin envelops the mass. This \u201Cskin\u201D shows no signs of natural growth
    and appears to function purely as a containment layer.\r\n\r\nNo organs have
    been conclusively identified ouside of his eyes.\r\n\r\nBehavior\r\n\r\nThe Spiner
    exhibits prolonged stalking behavior, remaining just outside direct observation.
    Subjects report a strong sensation of being watched well before visual contact
    is established.\r\n\r\nThe entity may emits sounds that vary between individuals.
    Analysis suggests the Spiner does not imitate distress or fear, but instead reproduces
    sounds the target finds deeply comforting. The mechanism appears reflexive and
    organic rather than deliberate.\r\n\r\nOnce contact is made, the Spiner may restrain
    and transport the subject.\r\nNotably, captured individuals describe the experience
    as calm, controlled, and in some cases comforting. No immediate physical harm
    is observed during transport.\r\n\r\nSubjects can be forcibly released if the
    entity sustains damage.\r\n\r\nNotes\r\n\r\nRepeated encounters imply the Spiner
    reacts unpredictably to lethal force.\r\nField reports consistently end after
    attempted termination.\r\n\r\nMY notes:\nDO NOT KILL.Sigurd"
